<br>
I recently started an Infiltrator, and I was wondering if anyone could reccomend which of the Weapon Types I should go into (Slash, Pierce, etc).  I ask because with Midgard, I picked axes...and while I love em, when compared to swords, they are just a pain to find. So many Sword drops, so little skill. So I would like to get a more common weapon type when in Albion...any thoughts?<br>
<br>
Thanks. <p><center><a href="http://www.legacyguild.net"target="_blank"><img src="http://snootorama.homestead.com/files/dycesig.jpg" border="0"></a><br></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uliloxficktjuv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lilox Ficktjuv</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 4:00:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1993.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> i picked...</span><hr size=1> When i started out, i made a saracen and thought that high dex low str, easy choise = thrust... but, as ive read on some boards it seems that slash would be the better choise for 2 reasons : <br>
<br>
1, someone said that the damage dome by CS styles is determined by the skill of CS you have, and by the DPS of your weapon, since slash weapons have higher DPS then thrust weapons (although suffering on the speed side) out opening and class defining styles would do more damage with a slashing spec then a thrusting spec.<br>
<br>
2, the styles you get from thrusting all have some prerequisite after the lvl 18 style, and going with slash you get a &quot;use any time&quot; style at 29 (that some say are one of the better styles of the game)<br>
<br>
and.... some say that more slashing weapons drop in game then thrusting weapons at higher level... <br>
<br>
now, at lvl 17, im thinking of rerolling and go with a briton inf, with slash specs... <br>
<br>
Aragrim, percival<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucaithcaidh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caith Caidh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 4:14:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1993.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: i picked...</span><hr size=1> Just a point, but I'm not so sure that PA bonus is affected at all by weapon delay or dps at the moment.  Need to do more testing to be sure though.  I'm not so sure that there's any advantage to going with a strength based weapon, especially when giving up partial dex base is taken into account.<br>
<br>
 <p><IMG SRC="http://www.dopplex.net/sigfile2.jpg" ALT="Caith Caidh, 35th Season Nightshade, An Claidheamh Soluis" ALIGN="middle"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulandril77.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Landril77</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 5:01:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1993.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: i picked...</span><hr size=1> Not sure how exactly the bonus is efected by dps and spd, but the max damage done with PA definately is.  <br>
<br>
At level 40, with a 36 CS skill my PA maxes out at 539 damage using a frozen heart piercer(thrust)  Speaking with a level 40 slashing infiltrator the other day I was told that he caps at slightly over 600.<br>
<br>
Granted, my CS skill could be a little higher, potentially gaining 36 more to my cap, but still falling short of the slasher.  From speaking with the other rogue, I think I put out slightly higher damage overall, and am a bit more effective pve with the thrust weapons, but my potential to 1-shot kill people is less.<br>
<br>
If I were to do it over again, I think I would go slashing.  I am happy with my thrust infiltrator as well though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucaithcaidh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caith Caidh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 5:16:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1993.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: i picked...</span><hr size=1> To put it another way - Our damage cap *IS* affected by weapon.  However, bonus on PA I believe isn't.  Thus, if you test on something that you will cap with (i.e. low greys) you will see better results with a higher dps, higher delay weapon.<br>
<br>
-Caith <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukeryath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keryath</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.twitchmonkey.com/~damnskippy/DAoC/kerface.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/2/02 3:19:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1993.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.twitchmonkey.com/~damnskippy/DAoC/kerface.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: i picked...</span><hr size=1> I went thrust, since it's the people in chain I expect to need the extra damage for. However, if you're mainly planning on taking out other assassins, slash is the way to go. <p><center><img src=http://www.twitchmonkey.com/~damnskippy/DAoC/kerysmall2.jpg></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse>The Safehouse</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19>Main Hall</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org">The Safehouse website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.guildboss.com"><img
